snippet.textDisplay: Hi Jeffree, I tried posting this comment on your newest Instagram post multiple times when you first posted and this morning, but my action was and is still blocked for some reason. Your post said to drop your cash apps in order to help 5 people out really in need at the moment. I also reached out through your DM’s. 🥺 I love and support you a ton. I’d be grateful for anything and would be really happy if you even glanced over my comment. My grandparents need help. I don’t like asking for my money but my grandparents have struggled their whole lives and my grandma is very sick. Before I explain, I’m really sorry there are those taking advantage of you with your generosity. Your prayers would even be enough. My grandma is currently undergoing chemotherapy, soon radiation every week for 11 weeks for her breast cancer (though it was removed). Although healthcare is free in Canada, her and my grandpa are really struggling financially right now and they live in a small town. My grandma is really sick and miserable and depressed because of it. I’ve never seen her this way before and she’s always such a hopeful and positive person. Both my grandparents are currently unemployed and all the money they have has been in savings for years, for their pensions. My grandma is 56 and my grandpa is 60. On top of that, my grandma can’t come into contact with others, especially during this difficult time because of her immune system. I don’t like asking for things but for the sake of my grandparents, anything would be greatly appreciated in order to help them out. They live in a different province, 5 hours away from us. My mother took her to her chemo appointment, which is a few hours away from where my grandma lives on Thursday, in order to give my grandfather a break and the opportunity to catch up on some of the work he is doing for others to make money. My grandma wouldn’t even let my mom take her car, wouldn’t let my mom pay gas money, paid for MY MOM’s meal, as she insisted and begged my mom, and won’t accept any money we are giving them. I have never seen her/them like this before and it breaks me. I really want to help my grandparents. We are doing what we can but we don’t live close by to help them enough. On top of that, my auntie is a LPN at the hospital where they live, so her and her family can’t come into contact with my grandma, as we don’t know if my aunt has gotten or will get anything. Both my aunt and uncle and grandparents live in a very small town in northern Saskatchewan. My grandparents aren’t working right now, like I said. My grandpa was laid off a few months ago and is trying to make money on the side by fixing cars for people in the community. I’m a huge supporter and would really appreciate it more than anything if you considered them during this difficult time. They have always been struggling since my mom and uncle were little. Before my grandpa was laid off, he worked for different employers on and off as a logger, waking up at 4 am everyday, working until 10pm and he would gone for 2 weeks at a time at camp.
